          </head>
          <msContents>
            <summary/>
            <textLang mainLang="syr">Syriac</textLang>
            <msItem xml:id="a1" n="1" defective="unknown">
              <locus from="1b" to="10a">Foll. 1b-10a</locus>
              
              <title type="supplied">A chronological introduction</title>
            </msItem>
            <msItem xml:id="a2" n="2" defective="true">
              <locus from="10a" to="69">Foll. 10a-69</locus>
              <author ref="http://syriaca.org/person/354">Athanasius of Alexandria</author>
              <title type="supplied">The Festal Letters of Athanasius</title>
              <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܐܓܪ̈ܬܐ ܥܐ̈ܕܢܝܬܐ ܕܩܕܝܫܐ ܡܪܝ ܐܬܢܣܝܘܣ<locus from="10a" to="10a"/>
              </rubric>
              <note>These letters were printed by Dr. Cureton in the order of their discovery, <bibl>Cureton, London, 1848</bibl>; and re-edited, in correct sequence and with a Latin translation, by Cardinal Mai in his <bibl>Nova Patrum Bibliotheca, tom. vi.</bibl> (see also <bibl>Migne, Patrol. Cursus Complet., Ser. Graeca, t. ii. col. 1339, etc.</bibl>). They were translated into German by <bibl>Dr. Larsow, Leipzig, 1852</bibl>; and into English by <bibl>Dr. Burgess, in Dr. Pusey's Library of Fathers of the Holy Catholic Church, 1854</bibl>, where the two leaves (foll. <locus from="41">41</locus> and <locus from="48">48</locus>) are printed, which were added to the manuscript since the appearance of the Curetonian text.</note>
              <note>Of the letters only twenty remain, the last of which is imperfect.</note>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
          <physDesc>
            <p>Vellum, about 10 7/8 in. by 7 7/8, consisting of 69 leaves, several of which are slightly soiled, the first being also torn. The quires, signed with letters, are now 7 in number. There are from 26 to 33 lines in each page. </p>
