            <decoDesc/>
            <additions>
              <p/>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <locus from="1a" to="1a"/>
                  <ref target="#handNote2"/>
                  <p>On fol. 1 a there is written in large, open characters, a note stating that the book belonged to the convent of S. Mary Deipara:</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">.ܐܝܬܘܗܝ ܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ ܠܕܝܪܐ ܩܕ܏ܝܫ ܕܝܠܕܬ ܐܠܗܐ ܕܒܡܕܒܪܐ ܕܐܣܩ̈ܝܛܝܣ ܟܠ ܕܩܪܐ ܢܨ̇ܠ̣ܐ ܥܠܝ ܡܛܠ ܡܪܢ</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition2" n="2">
                  <locus from="1b" to="1b"/>
                  <ref target="#handNote3"/>
                  <p>From a note on the margin of fol. 1 b it appears that a history of the blessed Virgin and a life of Simeon Stylites (<ref target="https://bl.syriac.uk/ms/169">Add. 14,484</ref>?) were at one time bound with these letters.</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">.ܘܬܘܒ ܬܫܥܝܬܐ ܕܝ̇ܠܕܬ ܐܠܗܐ. ܘܕܫܡܥܘܢ ܕܐܣܛܘܼܢܐ</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition3" n="3">
                  <locus from="1b" to="1b"/>
                  <ref target="#handNote4"/>
                  <p>On the same page a poor monk named Jacob has recorded his inability to understand the introduction in these words:</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">.܀ܐܓܪܬܐ ܕܐܬܢܣܝܘܣ ܀ ܐܢܐ ܝܥܩܘܒ ܚ̇ܛܝܐ ܩ̇ܪܝܬ ܠܗܕܐ ܐܓܪܬܐ ܘܠܐ ܝ̇ܕܥ ܐܢܐ ܡܘܢ ܐ̇ܡܪܐ ܫܒܘܩ ܠܝ</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
